  "texts": [
    "Later, Sprenger et al.",
    "45 demonstrated that divided attention could lead to a reduced number of alternative hypotheses generated or errors, bias, or limitations during information retrieval, and further lead to errors or bias in judgment by using the same framework.",
    "The results were also confirmed by Dasgupta et al.",
    "46 with additional experiments and simulations.",
    "Donnelly et al."
  ]
